<p class="svelte-1lcnmxv">The quote at the start of this article comes from <a href="https://www.loc.gov/item/sn83027091/" target="_blank">The Colored American</a>, an African-American led weekly publication based in Washinton and founded in 1893. The quote comes from a review of the &quot;American Negro Exhibit&quot; at the Paris Exposition, published in the 3rd November 1900 edition. This, and other copies of The Colored American, are also held by the Library of Congress and can be viewed online <a href="https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83027091/issues/first_pages/" target="_blank">here</a>.</p> 
